    "updated_at": "2016-06-13T18:21:01Z",
    "body": "Okay was able to reproduce in a new example app. There are two things which cause this to happen.\n1. The window must currently be hidden\n2. You must call `capturePage` asynchronously\n\n``` javascript\nvar app = require('electron').app;\nvar BrowserWindow = require('electron').BrowserWindow;\n\nvar mainWindow = null;\n\napp.on('ready', function() {\n  var opts = {\n    width: 1280,\n    height: 720,\n    show: false,\n    frame: false,\n    devTools: false\n  }\n\n  mainWindow = new BrowserWindow(opts);\n\n  // hiding the window is key, if it is shown it will work\n  mainWindow.hide()\n\n  mainWindow.loadURL('file://' + __dirname + '/index.html');\n\n  setTimeout(function(){\n    mainWindow.capturePage(function(data){\n        // this function is never called\n        console.log(\"captured data\", data)\n    })\n  }, 1000) // calling this async is key. if you reduce the setTimeout value it will work\n\n});\n```\n"
